WEBVTT

00:01:29.850 --> 00:01:34.930
[Our Dazzling Days]

00:01:35.280 --> 00:01:37.770
[Episode 15]

00:01:46.000 --> 00:01:46.660
Uncle Ding.

00:01:48.590 --> 00:01:50.229
Don't be discouraged, Uncle Ding.

00:01:50.229 --> 00:01:51.870
As the old saying goes,

00:01:52.200 --> 00:01:54.680
victory and defeat are common in battle.

00:01:55.070 --> 00:01:57.070
Next time, we'll get that shot first

00:01:57.310 --> 00:01:58.509
and then go mess with them.

00:01:58.509 --> 00:01:59.710
Don't worry about it.

00:02:01.790 --> 00:02:04.920
But I can't win back my pride
at the cost of my conscience.

00:02:05.070 --> 00:02:07.400
How could I possibly take someone's
emergency meds for some testosterone?

00:02:07.400 --> 00:02:08.310
We won't do that.

00:02:08.310 --> 00:02:10.150
I'll buy more for you when I get paid.

00:02:10.150 --> 00:02:12.880
Now that would really be
a waste of testosterone.

00:02:13.840 --> 00:02:15.030
What did you just call me?

00:02:15.030 --> 00:02:15.690
Uncle Ding.

00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:17.360
Why are you still calling me "Uncle Ding"?

00:02:17.360 --> 00:02:18.190
What else should I call you?

00:02:18.190 --> 00:02:19.360
You've joined the plant.

00:02:19.360 --> 00:02:21.000
You're an honorable worker now.

00:02:21.000 --> 00:02:23.930
In the plant, you can't call me
"Uncle Ding" anymore.

00:02:23.960 --> 00:02:24.960
Drop the "Uncle."

00:02:25.190 --> 00:02:26.240
Call me "Mentor."

00:02:26.760 --> 00:02:28.390
"Mentor" sounds a bit weird.

00:02:28.530 --> 00:02:29.840
I've called you Uncle Ding for years.

00:02:29.840 --> 00:02:30.710
It's affectionate and nice.

00:02:30.710 --> 00:02:32.370
Can't you be a bit more proper?

00:02:36.400 --> 00:02:36.910
Okay.

00:02:38.400 --> 00:02:39.520
Here, Mentor!

00:02:40.079 --> 00:02:40.910
Please have some tea,

00:02:40.910 --> 00:02:41.400
Mentor.

00:02:42.400 --> 00:02:43.000
You boy.

00:02:43.640 --> 00:02:44.310
This isn't mine.

00:02:44.310 --> 00:02:45.640
It's been here for days.

00:02:46.190 --> 00:02:47.240
Sit down. Sit.

00:02:50.800 --> 00:02:52.400
Who the hell drinks while on shift?

00:02:52.400 --> 00:02:53.060
Shi?

00:02:54.120 --> 00:02:54.710
Shi!

00:02:54.710 --> 00:02:55.280
Mentor,

00:02:55.310 --> 00:02:55.960
who would you like to see?

00:02:55.960 --> 00:02:57.190
Shi! Get Shi for me!

00:02:57.310 --> 00:02:57.970
Sure thing!

00:03:04.360 --> 00:03:05.190
Two Aces. Say "strong hand."

00:03:05.190 --> 00:03:06.240
-Yeah, strong hand.
-Can't beat that.

00:03:06.240 --> 00:03:07.640
Stop playing! Stop. Shi!

00:03:07.910 --> 00:03:08.910
Mentor is looking for you.

00:03:08.910 --> 00:03:09.360
Go quickly.

00:03:09.360 --> 00:03:10.520
Two Threes! I gotta go!

00:03:10.520 --> 00:03:11.630
Stick it on your face! Don't cheat!

00:03:11.630 --> 00:03:12.520
I'll be right back!

00:03:12.520 --> 00:03:14.050
Don't cheat while I'm gone!

00:03:14.110 --> 00:03:15.080
D-Don't leave the seat empty.

00:03:15.080 --> 00:03:16.280
You take over. Go. Go!

00:03:17.400 --> 00:03:17.870
Mentor.

00:03:18.750 --> 00:03:20.120
Come here. Have you been drinking?

00:03:20.120 --> 00:03:22.000
No, I haven't. I-I didn't drink today.

00:03:22.000 --> 00:03:23.200
Let me introduce you.

00:03:23.470 --> 00:03:25.130
This is your junior, Xiaoman.

00:03:26.190 --> 00:03:27.450
He's your senior, Shi.

00:03:27.820 --> 00:03:28.360
Nice to meet you, Senior.

00:03:28.360 --> 00:03:30.090
You're really something, man.

00:03:33.860 --> 00:03:35.240
You're coughing. Can't you smoke less?

00:03:35.240 --> 00:03:36.630
Is cutting back a little
really going to kill you?

00:03:36.630 --> 00:03:38.360
Sooner or later,
you'll cough your lungs out!

00:03:38.360 --> 00:03:38.800
No.

00:03:39.590 --> 00:03:40.390
Look, Mentor.

00:03:40.730 --> 00:03:42.590
I've got cough syrup in my left hand

00:03:42.590 --> 00:03:43.910
and the cigarette in my right.

00:03:43.910 --> 00:03:45.000
In from the left, out from the right—

00:03:45.000 --> 00:03:46.750
it's all about
total intake management, right?

00:03:46.750 --> 00:03:48.280
They cancel each other out.

00:03:48.520 --> 00:03:49.360
Xiaoman, have a cigarette?

00:03:49.360 --> 00:03:50.870
No, no, I don't smoke.

00:03:51.230 --> 00:03:51.870
Stop talking nonsense.

00:03:51.870 --> 00:03:53.470
Tell him about the work here.

00:03:54.010 --> 00:03:54.810
Sit down. Sit.

00:03:54.910 --> 00:03:55.370
Come on.

00:03:55.430 --> 00:03:56.090
Scoot over.

00:03:56.590 --> 00:03:57.920
The work here is simple.

00:03:58.590 --> 00:03:59.850
One shift, ten people.

00:04:00.380 --> 00:04:01.750
Five work in the morning,

00:04:01.750 --> 00:04:02.870
while the other five are "on vacation."

00:04:02.870 --> 00:04:04.190
Then after lunch,

00:04:04.190 --> 00:04:06.190
the two groups swap. Simple as that.

00:04:06.310 --> 00:04:08.570
"Vacation?" Where do we go for vacation?

00:04:08.910 --> 00:04:10.240
Right here in the plant.

00:04:10.560 --> 00:04:11.620
We just play poker.

00:04:12.000 --> 00:04:13.240
Do you know how to play "Queen"?

00:04:13.240 --> 00:04:14.310
Singles beat singles, pairs beat pairs...

00:04:14.310 --> 00:04:15.640
Say something serious.

00:04:16.310 --> 00:04:17.510
The three key points.

00:04:18.600 --> 00:04:19.390
When playing "Queen,"

00:04:19.390 --> 00:04:20.310
first, no straights.

00:04:20.310 --> 00:04:20.950
Second, no four of a kind.

00:04:20.950 --> 00:04:22.190
Third, no betting money.

00:04:22.190 --> 00:04:23.390
Otherwise, it'd be gambling.

00:04:23.390 --> 00:04:24.450
Am I right, Mentor?

00:04:29.310 --> 00:04:30.870
The real three key points are these.

00:04:30.870 --> 00:04:32.000
You must keep them in mind.

00:04:32.000 --> 00:04:32.830
First,

00:04:32.870 --> 00:04:35.130
be extra careful during the night shift.

00:04:35.920 --> 00:04:37.720
Accidents happen most easily
in the early morning—

00:04:37.720 --> 00:04:39.070
everyone's sleepy and exhausted.

00:04:39.070 --> 00:04:39.600
Second,

00:04:39.600 --> 00:04:42.600
if there's an accident,
never crowd around the scene.

00:04:42.720 --> 00:04:44.950
Find the upwind side
and get out of there fast.

00:04:44.950 --> 00:04:46.310
If you really can't tell
which direction is safe,

00:04:46.310 --> 00:04:48.040
lick your finger and hold it up—

00:04:48.120 --> 00:04:49.800
don't run toward the cool side.

00:04:49.800 --> 00:04:50.240
Okay.

00:04:50.630 --> 00:04:51.270
Third,

00:04:51.310 --> 00:04:52.570
and most importantly,

00:04:52.720 --> 00:04:54.920
never work a shift with reckless idiots

00:04:54.920 --> 00:04:56.600
who are sloppy with their work.

00:04:56.600 --> 00:04:57.630
Even if you're careful,

00:04:57.630 --> 00:04:58.830
one slip-up from them

00:04:58.870 --> 00:05:00.390
could still cost you your life.

00:05:00.390 --> 00:05:01.520
Got it. Understood.

00:05:01.950 --> 00:05:03.160
Mentor, you two keep talking.

00:05:03.160 --> 00:05:05.920
Then what does a typical reckless idiot
look like?

00:05:05.920 --> 00:05:07.980
You talk. I... I'll step out for a bit.

00:05:09.920 --> 00:05:11.320
Give your junior a smile.

00:05:11.800 --> 00:05:13.860
Why would I smile at him for no reason?

00:05:16.120 --> 00:05:19.720
Well, you're looking at a pretty textbook
reckless idiot right here.

00:05:19.720 --> 00:05:20.360
Piss off.

00:05:23.390 --> 00:05:24.560
I'm telling you—work is work!

00:05:24.560 --> 00:05:25.750
Stop joking around all the time!

00:05:25.750 --> 00:05:26.270
Gosh.

00:05:27.070 --> 00:05:28.530
I'm talking to those guys.

00:05:28.600 --> 00:05:29.460
Did you hear me?

00:05:29.800 --> 00:05:30.530
My goodness.

00:05:31.870 --> 00:05:33.120
I'd like to make a call.

00:05:33.120 --> 00:05:33.560
Okay.

00:05:42.830 --> 00:05:45.159
Um, I'm looking for Yan Xiaodan.

00:05:48.920 --> 00:05:50.120
Hello, Xiaoman?

00:05:50.720 --> 00:05:51.250
Xiaodan.

00:05:52.630 --> 00:05:54.390
How was your first day at work?

00:05:54.750 --> 00:05:56.070
I was just about to tell you.

00:05:56.070 --> 00:05:57.240
Back when we were in school,

00:05:57.240 --> 00:05:58.870
didn't we hear "Ode to the Motherland"

00:05:58.870 --> 00:06:00.400
almost every day on the way?

00:06:00.920 --> 00:06:03.510
Today, on my way to work,
it felt so different.

00:06:03.750 --> 00:06:05.360
When I heard the song on my way to work,

00:06:05.360 --> 00:06:06.950
I got really emotional.

00:06:07.430 --> 00:06:08.560
And I kept thinking to myself,

00:06:08.560 --> 00:06:10.680
I have to do something meaningful
at the plant.

00:06:10.680 --> 00:06:12.070
I have to repay my country.

00:06:12.070 --> 00:06:13.470
Do you know that feeling?

00:06:13.560 --> 00:06:14.430
I do.

00:06:14.870 --> 00:06:17.070
Do you know how
much they set my salary at?

00:06:17.070 --> 00:06:17.600
How much?

00:06:18.240 --> 00:06:21.270
Five hundred fifty-one yuan seventy fen,

00:06:21.270 --> 00:06:22.930
plus a twenty yuan allowance,

00:06:23.560 --> 00:06:25.800
and four yuan for the haircut fee.

00:06:26.000 --> 00:06:27.070
That's nearly 600 yuan.

00:06:27.070 --> 00:06:28.360
That much?

00:06:28.830 --> 00:06:30.270
That's a lot for you!

00:06:30.680 --> 00:06:31.280
By the way,

00:06:31.680 --> 00:06:33.600
I have some good news to share as well.

00:06:33.600 --> 00:06:34.200
What is it?

00:06:34.270 --> 00:06:36.950
My design work got exhibited.

00:06:37.070 --> 00:06:38.830
That's amazing! I've always said

00:06:38.830 --> 00:06:39.870
you're a natural.

00:06:40.070 --> 00:06:40.870
Whatever you do, you excel at it.

00:06:40.870 --> 00:06:42.270
But my inspiration

00:06:42.510 --> 00:06:44.840
came from the "Mahavira Hall" you gave me.

00:06:45.120 --> 00:06:47.650
So you deserve some credit
for this award too.

00:06:48.240 --> 00:06:49.680
How do I deserve any credit?

00:06:49.680 --> 00:06:50.950
I modeled it

00:06:51.270 --> 00:06:53.530
after the Mahavira Hall when I welded it.

00:06:53.680 --> 00:06:54.480
It was nothing special.

00:06:54.480 --> 00:06:55.750
Anyway, I'm happy for you.

00:06:55.750 --> 00:06:56.430
Keep it up.

00:06:58.120 --> 00:06:59.120
Xiaodan, hurry up.

00:06:59.120 --> 00:07:00.580
We're all waiting for you!

00:07:01.480 --> 00:07:02.190
Coming!

00:07:02.600 --> 00:07:03.360
I have to go.

00:07:03.360 --> 00:07:04.160
My classmates are calling me.

00:07:04.160 --> 00:07:04.720
Okay, okay.

00:07:04.720 --> 00:07:05.720
Let's talk later.

00:07:06.240 --> 00:07:07.390
Bye. Miss you.

00:07:10.300 --> 00:07:15.450
[East Integrated Chemical Plant]

00:07:15.600 --> 00:07:17.660
Cover me! I'm about to finish my hand!

00:07:17.830 --> 00:07:19.560
Can you only play a King?

00:07:20.040 --> 00:07:21.160
Come on, play something higher!

00:07:21.160 --> 00:07:23.120
Didn't I tell you to
play something higher?

00:07:23.120 --> 00:07:25.120
Wait, don't you have any high cards?

00:07:25.750 --> 00:07:26.950
Snack on sunflower seeds all you want,

00:07:26.950 --> 00:07:28.360
but stop throwing the shells
on the floor, okay?

00:07:28.360 --> 00:07:29.360
I just swept it,

00:07:29.360 --> 00:07:30.770
and you've made a mess again.

00:07:30.770 --> 00:07:32.960
Xiaoman, you're cleaning for nothing.

00:07:32.960 --> 00:07:33.510
Move over a bit.

00:07:33.510 --> 00:07:35.800
We'll have it back to a mess in no time.

00:07:36.070 --> 00:07:37.159
Lift your feet.

00:07:37.950 --> 00:07:39.480
If you have nothing to do...

00:07:39.920 --> 00:07:40.920
go fetch a pot of hot water.

00:07:40.920 --> 00:07:42.070
Then everyone can have hot tea
when they get here.

00:07:42.070 --> 00:07:43.120
Wouldn't that be nice?

00:07:43.120 --> 00:07:43.720
Right?

00:07:44.720 --> 00:07:46.750
Aren't you supposed to
fetch hot water this week?

00:07:46.750 --> 00:07:48.280
Who are you bossing around?

00:07:48.630 --> 00:07:49.690
-Mentor.
-Mentor.

00:07:50.080 --> 00:07:50.720
Come tidy up!

00:07:50.720 --> 00:07:53.480
I thought I'd let him bond with everyone,

00:07:53.510 --> 00:07:54.720
mixing in with the group.

00:07:54.720 --> 00:07:56.050
S-Something like that.

00:07:56.950 --> 00:08:00.390
Right now, I've got all this skill
and nowhere to put it to use,

00:08:00.390 --> 00:08:01.160
you know?

00:08:02.400 --> 00:08:03.860
Let's play poker for a bit?

00:08:04.310 --> 00:08:05.680
Playing poker first thing in the morning?

00:08:05.680 --> 00:08:07.080
Am I being too easy on you?

00:08:08.160 --> 00:08:10.190
What else can we do?

00:08:10.950 --> 00:08:11.560
Mentor,

00:08:12.160 --> 00:08:15.290
has our factory always been like this?
Rotating shifts?

00:08:15.830 --> 00:08:16.640
Not always.

00:08:17.480 --> 00:08:19.510
We were pretty busy before the Gulf War.

00:08:19.510 --> 00:08:22.170
It's only been like this
for the last couple of years.

00:08:22.170 --> 00:08:23.240
Look how idle everyone is.

00:08:23.240 --> 00:08:25.080
Every day, it's just eating
sunflower seeds or playing poker.

00:08:25.080 --> 00:08:27.210
Look at how many seeds they eat all day.

00:08:34.080 --> 00:08:36.630
There's really nothing to do in our plant?

00:08:37.120 --> 00:08:38.510
Are none of the machines broken?

00:08:38.510 --> 00:08:39.960
No maintenance or repairs to do?

00:08:39.960 --> 00:08:41.960
We're all resting here.

00:08:43.440 --> 00:08:44.200
Wanna work?

00:08:45.150 --> 00:08:46.210
What work is there?

00:08:46.630 --> 00:08:47.390
Repair work.

00:08:48.190 --> 00:08:48.870
I'll take you along.

00:08:48.870 --> 00:08:49.360
Sure.

00:08:49.510 --> 00:08:50.970
-Let's go.
-Are you going?

00:08:51.480 --> 00:08:52.550
Mentor, I don't want to.

00:08:52.550 --> 00:08:54.510
M-My back hurts, and I keep coughing.

00:08:54.510 --> 00:08:55.000
I'm telling you,

00:08:55.000 --> 00:08:56.320
you can't play poker if you don't go.

00:08:56.320 --> 00:08:57.620
We won't play. We won't.

00:08:57.620 --> 00:08:58.050
You go.

00:08:58.080 --> 00:08:59.410
Go ahead and crack them.

00:09:00.270 --> 00:09:01.000
Come on.

00:09:01.000 --> 00:09:02.000
Let's play poker.

00:09:02.080 --> 00:09:03.540
Keep it down. Keep it down.

00:09:12.320 --> 00:09:12.750
Be careful.

00:09:12.750 --> 00:09:13.240
Okay.

00:09:14.550 --> 00:09:14.980
Oh my.

00:09:17.390 --> 00:09:17.940
Look.

00:09:20.390 --> 00:09:21.320
A little vegetable patch.

00:09:21.320 --> 00:09:22.830
These rows are chili peppers.

00:09:22.830 --> 00:09:24.360
I was thinking of
clearing out that side later

00:09:24.360 --> 00:09:26.440
and planting some tomatoes and eggplants.

00:09:26.440 --> 00:09:27.270
Shi is so lazy

00:09:27.270 --> 00:09:28.080
and doesn't want to do anything.

00:09:28.080 --> 00:09:29.270
It's perfect that you're here.

00:09:29.270 --> 00:09:30.070
Just perfect.

00:09:32.000 --> 00:09:33.660
What are we here for? Farming?

00:09:36.190 --> 00:09:37.830
Didn't you say there was some repair work?

00:09:37.830 --> 00:09:39.030
Repairing the earth.

00:09:39.420 --> 00:09:40.520
You guys are so funny.

00:09:40.520 --> 00:09:41.240
Repairing the Earth...

00:09:41.240 --> 00:09:42.000
T-This is just farming.

00:09:42.000 --> 00:09:43.000
How are those the same thing?

00:09:43.000 --> 00:09:44.030
Just hurry up and work.

00:09:44.030 --> 00:09:44.810
T-Turn over the soil over there.

00:09:44.810 --> 00:09:45.540
Hurry up. Go.

00:09:45.960 --> 00:09:47.320
W-What kind of repair work is this?

00:09:47.320 --> 00:09:48.120
Get on with it!

00:09:50.670 --> 00:09:51.390
Jesus.

00:09:52.510 --> 00:09:54.310
You guys play poker all day long,

00:09:54.320 --> 00:09:55.240
while I'm here farming.

00:09:55.240 --> 00:09:56.480
If you want to sing, sing out loud!

00:09:56.480 --> 00:09:57.840
Stop mumbling over there!

00:09:57.840 --> 00:10:00.440
This... well... Where should I start?

00:10:04.150 --> 00:10:06.840
Mentor, here's how I see it.

00:10:07.760 --> 00:10:09.450
Well, I'm a worker,

00:10:09.480 --> 00:10:10.320
a technician,

00:10:10.560 --> 00:10:12.240
right? I joined the plant to do repairs.

00:10:12.240 --> 00:10:12.910
But now you're making me farm.

00:10:12.910 --> 00:10:14.240
Am I a worker or a farmer?

00:10:14.480 --> 00:10:15.550
In a sense,

00:10:15.910 --> 00:10:18.170
workers and farmers are one and the same.

00:10:18.240 --> 00:10:19.240
Hurry up and do it.

00:10:19.530 --> 00:10:20.320
It's busy back in the workshop.

00:10:20.320 --> 00:10:21.320
I'm heading back.

00:10:24.300 --> 00:10:25.520
Busy in the workshop?

00:10:25.550 --> 00:10:26.750
Busy playing cards.

00:10:55.440 --> 00:10:57.910
Captain, slacking off here, aren't you?

00:10:57.910 --> 00:10:58.510
You're back, Xia.

00:10:58.510 --> 00:10:59.750
-Mentor is back.
-Lying...

00:10:59.750 --> 00:11:01.210
All you know is lying down.

00:11:01.360 --> 00:11:03.490
Why don't you just go home and lie down?

00:11:04.080 --> 00:11:06.210
Xia, have you really made up your mind?

00:11:06.870 --> 00:11:07.390
Yes.

00:11:08.480 --> 00:11:09.510
Being self-employed isn't

00:11:09.510 --> 00:11:10.960
as easy as you think.

00:11:11.150 --> 00:11:11.840
Exactly.

00:11:12.000 --> 00:11:12.600
I know.

00:11:12.630 --> 00:11:14.750
Everyone says
we plant drivers have it made—

00:11:14.750 --> 00:11:16.440
three pedals at your feet,

00:11:16.510 --> 00:11:18.200
and you're somebody wherever you go.

00:11:18.200 --> 00:11:19.440
People are dying to get in.

00:11:19.440 --> 00:11:20.360
But look at you,

00:11:20.360 --> 00:11:21.360
you want to leave.

00:11:22.320 --> 00:11:23.780
I know what you're saying.

00:11:24.720 --> 00:11:25.390
But tell me,

00:11:26.120 --> 00:11:27.960
there's never enough work to do.

00:11:28.150 --> 00:11:30.270
We have nothing to do all day.

00:11:30.600 --> 00:11:31.980
What's the point in lying around

00:11:31.980 --> 00:11:33.240
like him?

00:11:33.270 --> 00:11:35.800
I've got all this energy
and nowhere to use it!

00:11:35.960 --> 00:11:37.320
And my wife also wants me

00:11:37.320 --> 00:11:38.920
to leave here and get moving.

00:11:39.270 --> 00:11:40.720
Now we're getting to it—

00:11:40.720 --> 00:11:41.910
it always comes down to your wife!

00:11:41.910 --> 00:11:43.510
Why are you so afraid of her?

00:11:43.510 --> 00:11:45.110
Scared of my wife? Nonsense!

00:11:45.270 --> 00:11:46.480
No, I just...

00:11:47.080 --> 00:11:47.960
I just...

00:11:48.820 --> 00:11:50.030
take a little advice

00:11:50.050 --> 00:11:51.320
from my wife now and then.

00:11:51.320 --> 00:11:53.320
I'm still the one calling the shots!

00:11:53.550 --> 00:11:55.000
And my son said

00:11:55.320 --> 00:11:56.930
he fully supports me
going out to try my luck.

00:11:56.930 --> 00:11:59.720
Xia, there's really not much work
right now,

00:12:00.080 --> 00:12:02.000
but at least the whole plant
is still running.

00:12:02.000 --> 00:12:03.650
It's somewhat of a safety net.

00:12:03.650 --> 00:12:04.290
I know.

00:12:05.240 --> 00:12:05.790
Mentor,

00:12:06.670 --> 00:12:07.840
how much of your daily earnings

00:12:07.840 --> 00:12:10.050
goes to the taxi company?

00:12:10.320 --> 00:12:12.720
Not much. 160 yuan a day
to the taxi company.

00:12:12.870 --> 00:12:15.600
See? I told you that's over 5,000 a month.

00:12:15.720 --> 00:12:18.000
Xia, you're working from dawn till dusk—

00:12:18.000 --> 00:12:19.200
what for?

00:12:19.880 --> 00:12:20.790
What for?

00:12:21.480 --> 00:12:23.080
To earn more money.

00:12:24.120 --> 00:12:24.720
All right.

00:12:25.570 --> 00:12:27.370
Oh, right, yeah, Captain, uh...

00:12:27.580 --> 00:12:28.870
the clutch is a bit loose,

00:12:28.870 --> 00:12:30.320
and the left headlight is very dim.

00:12:30.320 --> 00:12:32.320
Don't drive long distances
until it's fixed,

00:12:32.320 --> 00:12:33.150
especially at night.

00:12:33.150 --> 00:12:34.790
Don't worry. Tang,

00:12:34.960 --> 00:12:36.750
arrange for someone to fix it tomorrow.

00:12:36.750 --> 00:12:37.910
I'm on it immediately!

00:12:37.910 --> 00:12:38.370
I'm off.

00:12:38.440 --> 00:12:40.150
M-Mentor, let me help you pack.

00:12:40.150 --> 00:12:41.150
Xia! Xia!

00:12:41.270 --> 00:12:43.080
Here, these are for this month.

00:12:43.600 --> 00:12:44.260
Take these.

00:12:47.080 --> 00:12:48.080
What does it mean?

00:12:48.480 --> 00:12:49.670
Building from nothing—
but no need to go bare-handed?

00:12:49.670 --> 00:12:50.670
Something like that!

00:12:50.670 --> 00:12:52.400
Okay. Thanks for the blessing!

00:12:52.610 --> 00:12:54.320
I'll keep this pair as a keepsake. Thanks.

00:12:54.320 --> 00:12:55.750
Mentor, let me help you pack.

00:12:55.750 --> 00:12:57.000
Get lost. Get lost!

00:12:57.960 --> 00:12:59.550
I'm already done. Now he shows up to help.

00:12:59.550 --> 00:13:00.360
You brat.

00:13:00.510 --> 00:13:02.200
You need to teach him a lesson later.

00:13:02.200 --> 00:13:02.960
Mentor,

00:13:03.210 --> 00:13:05.480
whenever you have time,
come back and visit us.

00:13:05.480 --> 00:13:07.360
We're waiting for you
to have s-skewers together.

00:13:07.360 --> 00:13:08.510
Right. Treat us to skewers!

00:13:08.510 --> 00:13:09.320
Treat us to skewers.

00:13:09.320 --> 00:13:11.320
When I make money,
I'll treat you to skewers every day.

00:13:11.320 --> 00:13:12.240
Until you're sick of them.

00:13:12.240 --> 00:13:12.770
Alright.

00:13:12.960 --> 00:13:15.550
Xia, work hard now that you're out there.

00:13:15.960 --> 00:13:16.720
Absolutely!

00:13:17.510 --> 00:13:18.030
I'm off!

00:13:18.050 --> 00:13:19.510
Come back and visit often.

00:13:19.670 --> 00:13:20.240
Don't say anything anymore.

00:13:20.240 --> 00:13:21.750
You'll make me cry.

00:13:22.150 --> 00:13:23.720
Bye. Bye. Bye.

00:13:23.720 --> 00:13:24.870
-Bye, Mentor.
-Bye.

00:13:34.390 --> 00:13:35.080
Xiaodan.

00:13:35.630 --> 00:13:36.160
Xiaodan.

00:13:37.080 --> 00:13:38.810
Come on, come here for a second.

00:13:39.150 --> 00:13:40.280
I need to talk to you.

00:13:40.490 --> 00:13:40.950
Come on.

00:13:43.790 --> 00:13:44.850
What's wrong, sir?

00:13:45.480 --> 00:13:46.750
You remember the overseas study program

00:13:46.750 --> 00:13:48.280
I mentioned before, right?

00:13:48.720 --> 00:13:49.790
Can I really go?

00:13:50.000 --> 00:13:51.750
It's not guaranteed yet.

00:13:52.030 --> 00:13:53.230
It still needs approval
from the department,

00:13:53.230 --> 00:13:56.000
the university,
and the study-abroad program provider.

00:13:56.000 --> 00:13:57.120
Got it, sir.

00:13:57.600 --> 00:13:58.840
Alright, Xiaodan. Go back to class now.

00:13:58.840 --> 00:14:00.170
-Thank you.
-Good luck.

00:14:05.670 --> 00:14:06.270
Here, Shi.

00:14:10.390 --> 00:14:11.720
Lulu, is this amount right?

00:14:11.720 --> 00:14:13.320
I-I don't have a bonus again?

00:14:13.930 --> 00:14:15.320
You ask every single month.

00:14:15.320 --> 00:14:16.850
Can there always be a bonus?

00:14:17.750 --> 00:14:18.600
Hurry up.

00:14:18.720 --> 00:14:20.440
If there's none, there's none.

00:14:20.440 --> 00:14:20.970
I'm here.

00:14:21.910 --> 00:14:23.370
Here for your salary, huh?

00:14:24.550 --> 00:14:25.480
Here. Here's yours.

00:14:25.480 --> 00:14:26.080
Okay.

00:14:27.330 --> 00:14:27.920
Xiaoman!

00:14:28.320 --> 00:14:29.360
I'm warning you,

00:14:29.440 --> 00:14:31.120
you need to count your wages right here.

00:14:31.120 --> 00:14:32.550
If you leave this room
and then say something's wrong...

00:14:32.550 --> 00:14:33.610
I know. I trust you!

00:14:34.630 --> 00:14:35.830
I trust you too, Lulu.

00:14:36.000 --> 00:14:36.980
I trust you the most.

00:14:36.980 --> 00:14:37.510
No bonus.

00:14:37.510 --> 00:14:38.670
Wait, let me check.

00:14:38.910 --> 00:14:40.030
I worked hard.

00:14:43.820 --> 00:14:45.620
I'll count it myself. It's fine.

00:14:58.110 --> 00:15:00.710
What's wrong?
Why are you still standing here?

00:15:00.830 --> 00:15:02.630
I-I'll wait for you downstairs.

00:15:03.360 --> 00:15:04.510
Don't you know your place?

00:15:04.510 --> 00:15:05.000
Yes.

00:15:05.240 --> 00:15:05.550
Go.

00:15:05.820 --> 00:15:06.820
You can have this.

00:15:09.840 --> 00:15:10.440
Zhang Yao.

00:15:10.510 --> 00:15:12.030
Okay, let me check.

00:15:12.200 --> 00:15:13.960
W-Why did you just get a slip?

00:15:14.320 --> 00:15:15.850
I don't like carrying cash.

00:15:16.670 --> 00:15:17.670
Can't be bothered with it.

00:15:17.670 --> 00:15:19.270
I'm just here to pick up Lulu.

00:15:20.070 --> 00:15:20.750
Keep waiting here then.

00:15:20.750 --> 00:15:21.630
She's not done yet.

00:15:21.630 --> 00:15:22.000
Let's go.

00:15:22.000 --> 00:15:22.630
Aren't we waiting for a bit?

00:15:22.630 --> 00:15:23.150
No.

00:15:23.150 --> 00:15:23.720
No?

00:15:24.080 --> 00:15:26.340
Let me see... Let me see
if you got a bonus.

00:15:28.150 --> 00:15:29.080
Coming, coming!

00:15:30.550 --> 00:15:31.000
Uncle.

00:15:31.120 --> 00:15:31.790
Xiaoman!

00:15:33.030 --> 00:15:33.550
Come on in.

00:15:33.550 --> 00:15:34.000
Uncle.

00:15:34.150 --> 00:15:34.720
Come in.

00:15:35.840 --> 00:15:36.320
Auntie.

00:15:36.720 --> 00:15:37.410
You're knitting.

00:15:37.410 --> 00:15:38.670
Xiaoman, you're here.

00:15:39.270 --> 00:15:41.000
Uncle, come here.

00:15:42.630 --> 00:15:43.360
Um...

00:15:43.360 --> 00:15:43.890
Xiaoman.

00:15:44.320 --> 00:15:46.360
I got my first paycheck.

00:15:46.670 --> 00:15:47.470
That's great.

00:15:47.840 --> 00:15:49.080
I bought this for you.

00:15:49.790 --> 00:15:50.590
A bedding set!

00:15:51.720 --> 00:15:52.720
You silly child,

00:15:52.720 --> 00:15:54.000
why did you buy this?

00:15:54.000 --> 00:15:55.270
We have plenty of bedding.

00:15:55.270 --> 00:15:55.790
Yeah.

00:15:55.870 --> 00:15:56.870
Just use something new.

00:15:56.870 --> 00:15:57.440
What's the harm?

00:15:57.440 --> 00:15:58.510
It's hard to earn money.

00:15:58.510 --> 00:15:59.510
We appreciate the thought. We really do.

00:15:59.510 --> 00:16:00.370
Go return it.

00:16:00.480 --> 00:16:01.910
Save the money you've earned.

00:16:01.910 --> 00:16:02.150
Go on.

00:16:02.150 --> 00:16:03.270
Don't. It's a gift.

00:16:03.290 --> 00:16:04.000
Why return it? Take it.

00:16:04.000 --> 00:16:04.630
No, no.

00:16:04.630 --> 00:16:05.320
Why would I want it?

00:16:05.320 --> 00:16:06.840
What do I need it for?

00:16:07.600 --> 00:16:08.320
I tore the package.

00:16:08.320 --> 00:16:09.720
The package is torn.
It can't be r-returned now.

00:16:09.720 --> 00:16:10.240
Oh, you...

00:16:10.240 --> 00:16:11.440
You have to use it now.

00:16:11.440 --> 00:16:13.320
You're always playing these tricks.

00:16:13.320 --> 00:16:14.250
I'll put it here.

00:16:15.270 --> 00:16:17.150
Then go cook something for him then.

00:16:17.150 --> 00:16:17.910
-Okay.
-Eat here.

00:16:17.910 --> 00:16:18.510
I'm not eating here!

00:16:18.510 --> 00:16:19.320
It'll be ready in no time!

00:16:19.320 --> 00:16:19.840
I'm really not eating here!

00:16:19.840 --> 00:16:20.510
Have lunch here.

00:16:20.510 --> 00:16:21.440
Hurry, sit down.

00:16:22.630 --> 00:16:23.240
Sit.

00:16:25.050 --> 00:16:26.380
I'll get you some water.

00:16:26.600 --> 00:16:28.000
Don't trouble yourself, Auntie.

00:16:28.000 --> 00:16:29.080
Xia Lei isn't home,

00:16:29.080 --> 00:16:30.080
so isn't this all just

00:16:30.080 --> 00:16:31.340
what I should be doing?

00:16:33.550 --> 00:16:35.550
How are things with you and Xiaodan?

00:16:35.790 --> 00:16:37.270
We're fine.

00:16:37.670 --> 00:16:39.080
Same as usual.

00:16:41.870 --> 00:16:42.720
Honestly...

00:16:42.870 --> 00:16:44.120
Look at you kids,

00:16:45.240 --> 00:16:47.120
all grown up in the blink of an eye.

00:16:47.320 --> 00:16:48.120
Time flies.

00:16:49.270 --> 00:16:51.440
So, how's the work at the plant?

00:16:51.920 --> 00:16:53.600
It's okay for now,

00:16:53.790 --> 00:16:55.840
but there's just not much work.

00:16:56.200 --> 00:16:57.150
You just joined the plant,

00:16:57.150 --> 00:16:58.390
so don't rush to grab every task.
You hear me?

00:16:58.390 --> 00:16:58.910
I know.

00:16:58.910 --> 00:17:00.110
I know what I'm doing.

00:17:01.000 --> 00:17:02.240
Listen to your mentor in everything.

00:17:02.240 --> 00:17:04.030
Whatever else we might say about him,

00:17:04.030 --> 00:17:05.160
his skills are undeniable.

00:17:05.160 --> 00:17:05.880
For sure!

00:17:05.880 --> 00:17:07.810
I definitely have to listen to him.

00:17:08.640 --> 00:17:09.160
I forgot! I forgot!

00:17:09.160 --> 00:17:10.550
My mentor asked me to
go dig a vegetable cellar with him.

00:17:10.550 --> 00:17:11.310
I completely forgot.

00:17:11.310 --> 00:17:12.480
I need to get over there now!

00:17:12.480 --> 00:17:13.680
It won't hurt to eat first!

00:17:13.680 --> 00:17:14.810
-You should eat first!
-No!

00:17:14.810 --> 00:17:16.750
If I show up late,
he'll definitely kick me again!

00:17:16.750 --> 00:17:17.609
Uncle, I'm off!

00:17:18.010 --> 00:17:19.720
-It won't take long. Eat before you go!
-Bye!

00:17:19.720 --> 00:17:20.310
You guys eat. You guys eat.

00:17:20.310 --> 00:17:22.510
I've already started slicing the meat!

00:17:22.960 --> 00:17:23.720
This kid.

00:17:24.000 --> 00:17:25.240
Can you move a bit faster?

00:17:25.240 --> 00:17:26.160
Coming, coming!

00:17:26.160 --> 00:17:27.510
Who are you learning to work for?

00:17:27.510 --> 00:17:28.109
Are you learning for yourself

00:17:28.109 --> 00:17:28.830
or for me?

00:17:30.160 --> 00:17:32.000
We were thinking of
picking you up at your place!

00:17:32.000 --> 00:17:33.000
Stop blabbering!

00:17:34.920 --> 00:17:36.250
We also made tea for you.

00:17:36.270 --> 00:17:37.530
Hurry up and come over.

00:17:37.960 --> 00:17:39.620
We're digging a cellar today!

00:17:39.980 --> 00:17:41.310
Come over here. Come on.

00:17:42.960 --> 00:17:44.110
I've already picked the spot.

00:17:44.110 --> 00:17:45.350
I've also marked out and dug the circle.

00:17:45.350 --> 00:17:46.070
Later on, everyone,

00:17:46.070 --> 00:17:47.550
just dig inside this circle.

00:17:47.550 --> 00:17:48.460
A good cellar should be

00:17:48.460 --> 00:17:49.510
narrow at the top

00:17:49.510 --> 00:17:50.510
and wide at the bottom.

00:17:50.510 --> 00:17:51.350
That guarantees

00:17:51.350 --> 00:17:53.110
it stays warm in winter
and cool in summer.

00:17:53.110 --> 00:17:54.480
I've already dug the circle.

00:17:54.480 --> 00:17:55.540
Now, we'll take turns

00:17:55.540 --> 00:17:58.310
digging out... the rough frame first.

00:17:58.350 --> 00:17:59.080
Then, we'll use the shovels

00:17:59.080 --> 00:18:00.530
to dig deeper.

00:18:00.680 --> 00:18:01.920
Alright. Shi, you go first.

00:18:01.920 --> 00:18:03.580
Sure, sure. You rest, Mentor.

00:18:05.160 --> 00:18:06.160
Don't be so gross.

00:18:07.000 --> 00:18:08.310
I don't mind you.

00:18:08.960 --> 00:18:09.470
Come on!

00:18:13.790 --> 00:18:15.590
Watch your digging. Are you
digging the ground or digging at me?

00:18:15.590 --> 00:18:16.960
I've got good aim. I...

00:18:18.440 --> 00:18:18.830
I'm telling you,

00:18:18.830 --> 00:18:20.110
if you hit a high-voltage line,

00:18:20.110 --> 00:18:21.830
that's it. We'll be burying you today.

00:18:21.830 --> 00:18:22.510
Watch it!

00:18:24.590 --> 00:18:25.830
Put your back into it. Come on.

00:18:25.830 --> 00:18:27.490
Why are you just staring at me?

00:18:27.720 --> 00:18:29.780
Dig! J-Just looking won't dig a hole.

00:18:30.000 --> 00:18:31.480
Why are you just standing there?
Get digging!

00:18:31.480 --> 00:18:32.920
Why are you two just looking at it?

00:18:32.920 --> 00:18:33.750
Xiaoman.

00:18:34.610 --> 00:18:35.940
I can see it clearly now.

00:18:36.510 --> 00:18:38.480
The only one who can carry on my legacy

00:18:38.480 --> 00:18:39.310
is you.

00:18:40.160 --> 00:18:40.750
Mentor,

00:18:41.030 --> 00:18:43.680
I've learned everything at the plant—

00:18:43.680 --> 00:18:44.720
lathe work, plumbing, riveting, welding—

00:18:44.720 --> 00:18:47.050
but none of it
helps with digging a cellar.

00:18:47.680 --> 00:18:49.200
What's wrong with digging a cellar?

00:18:49.200 --> 00:18:50.790
That's a skill every man
from the Northeast needs,

00:18:50.790 --> 00:18:51.720
I'm telling you.

00:18:52.110 --> 00:18:52.920
If you know how to dig a cellar,

00:18:52.920 --> 00:18:55.200
that'll even save you some bride money,
you know?

00:18:55.200 --> 00:18:56.650
Wifey, is dinner ready?

00:18:56.830 --> 00:18:57.560
You're back!

00:18:57.640 --> 00:18:58.480
Wash up.

00:18:59.400 --> 00:19:00.790
Hurry up! Let's eat!

00:19:00.920 --> 00:19:02.250
The food is on the table!

00:19:03.530 --> 00:19:05.390
Hand out the chopsticks. Come on.

00:19:05.640 --> 00:19:06.100
Come on.

00:19:06.510 --> 00:19:07.160
So good.

00:19:07.510 --> 00:19:08.640
Mentor, no alcohol?

00:19:09.000 --> 00:19:10.400
We did so much work today.

00:19:10.420 --> 00:19:11.880
Let's have a drink to unwind.

00:19:11.880 --> 00:19:12.440
You want some?

00:19:12.440 --> 00:19:13.370
Let's have some.

00:19:13.920 --> 00:19:14.920
Go get us alcohol.

00:19:15.110 --> 00:19:16.110
You want alcohol?

00:19:16.680 --> 00:19:17.480
Which bottle?

00:19:18.030 --> 00:19:19.290
Why not get Xiaoman's?

00:19:19.310 --> 00:19:21.030
He just got you a bottle of liquor

00:19:21.030 --> 00:19:21.830
and a carton of cigarettes.

00:19:21.830 --> 00:19:23.030
Why did you buy those?

00:19:23.030 --> 00:19:24.070
Just get it. Get the one I bought.

00:19:24.070 --> 00:19:25.790
Fine. Go get it. Let's drink it.

00:19:25.790 --> 00:19:27.440
I'll go get it. Wait!

00:19:27.720 --> 00:19:28.640
You know the etiquette, kid.

00:19:28.640 --> 00:19:31.040
Come on, eat something. Fill your stomach.

00:19:32.000 --> 00:19:32.880
It's just... you know,

00:19:32.880 --> 00:19:34.720
a-a start.

00:19:35.070 --> 00:19:35.720
When autumn comes,

00:19:35.720 --> 00:19:37.450
I'll teach you the real skills.

00:19:38.720 --> 00:19:39.400
How is it?

00:19:39.790 --> 00:19:40.680
T-This baijiu won't do.

00:19:40.680 --> 00:19:41.680
No, no.

00:19:41.680 --> 00:19:42.480
This baijiu is so great.

00:19:42.480 --> 00:19:43.410
You bought this?

00:19:44.110 --> 00:19:45.020
Xiaoman, what are you doing?

00:19:45.020 --> 00:19:46.270
You can't spend money like this.

00:19:46.270 --> 00:19:47.110
You're

00:19:47.110 --> 00:19:48.110
throwing your money away.

00:19:48.110 --> 00:19:49.720
How many eggs is this thing worth?

00:19:49.720 --> 00:19:50.790
Well, eggs or not,

00:19:50.880 --> 00:19:52.810
no amount of eggs can get you drunk.

00:19:53.070 --> 00:19:53.880
It won't work.

00:19:54.240 --> 00:19:55.880
You have to be thrifty.

00:19:55.880 --> 00:19:57.510
You can't always spend like this.

00:19:57.510 --> 00:19:59.440
Mentor, this baijiu smells good.

00:20:01.150 --> 00:20:01.700
So good.

00:20:06.110 --> 00:20:07.510
Who told you to open it?

00:20:07.880 --> 00:20:09.960
Aren't we going to drink a bit to relax,

00:20:09.960 --> 00:20:12.310
so... I opened it as soon as I got it.

00:20:12.310 --> 00:20:13.590
You reckless fool!

00:20:14.510 --> 00:20:16.170
It's fine. It's already open.

00:20:18.240 --> 00:20:19.640
I-I'll put the cap back on.

00:20:19.640 --> 00:20:21.680
I was just trying to be diligent,
opening it,

00:20:21.680 --> 00:20:23.020
and now I'm getting scolded for it!

00:20:23.020 --> 00:20:25.680
Stop fussing with it.
That just cost three eggs.

00:20:28.070 --> 00:20:29.110
Why are you mad?

00:20:31.110 --> 00:20:31.640
What should we do?

00:20:31.640 --> 00:20:32.720
What do you think?

00:20:35.560 --> 00:20:37.680
Let's drink.
I'll have three eggs' worth first.

00:20:37.680 --> 00:20:38.480
I'll use this.

00:20:38.520 --> 00:20:40.110
Come on, Mentor, you scared me!

00:20:40.110 --> 00:20:40.980
Next time, you have to tell me first!

00:20:40.980 --> 00:20:41.960
You must tell me.

00:20:42.400 --> 00:20:43.310
How can you use a bowl?

00:20:43.310 --> 00:20:45.040
-Well...
-You... go easy on it!

00:20:59.480 --> 00:21:00.480
Where is Xiaoman?

00:21:01.700 --> 00:21:02.680
Xia Lei, give me a hand.

00:21:02.680 --> 00:21:04.340
Here, let me take that for you.

00:21:09.030 --> 00:21:10.030
Where is Xiaoman?

00:21:10.240 --> 00:21:10.970
I don't know.

00:21:12.960 --> 00:21:14.820
Didn't he say he'd come pick us up?

00:21:16.960 --> 00:21:17.550
Xiaodan!

00:21:17.720 --> 00:21:19.320
-Here he comes.
-I'm coming!

00:21:19.990 --> 00:21:22.250
-What are you doing?
-Xiaoman! Xiaoman!

00:21:23.680 --> 00:21:24.750
Xiaoman!

00:21:28.750 --> 00:21:29.310
Did you miss me?

00:21:29.310 --> 00:21:30.440
Yes? Did you miss me?

00:21:32.260 --> 00:21:33.190
I got bumped too.

00:21:34.510 --> 00:21:35.640
What's wrong with you two?

00:21:35.640 --> 00:21:37.510
-Our knees bumped.
-It really hurts.

00:21:37.510 --> 00:21:38.720
Our knees collided.

00:21:39.160 --> 00:21:39.890
Does it hurt?

00:21:39.920 --> 00:21:40.440
Yes.

00:21:40.640 --> 00:21:42.300
That hit made my knees go numb.

00:21:43.200 --> 00:21:46.160
What a dramatic reunion you two have.

00:21:46.880 --> 00:21:49.270
Yeah. We crashed into each other
as soon as we met.

00:21:49.270 --> 00:21:50.160
Come on, let's go.

00:21:50.160 --> 00:21:51.680
Your dad is waiting at the entrance.

00:21:51.680 --> 00:21:52.160
He's outside, huh.

00:21:52.160 --> 00:21:52.740
Let's go then. I'll carry one.

00:21:52.740 --> 00:21:53.540
I'll take one.

00:21:55.480 --> 00:21:56.410
It really hurts.

00:21:56.680 --> 00:21:57.680
What do you want to eat
now that you're back?

00:21:57.680 --> 00:21:59.080
I want to eat everything.

00:21:59.670 --> 00:22:00.640
Is there anything specific you want?

00:22:00.640 --> 00:22:01.770
So we can prepare it.

00:22:02.960 --> 00:22:03.720
Made by you?

00:22:04.310 --> 00:22:04.920
Made by me?

00:22:05.880 --> 00:22:07.160
Made by Xia Lei's dad, then.

00:22:07.160 --> 00:22:07.640
Okay.

00:22:07.880 --> 00:22:08.550
I want to eat it all.

00:22:08.550 --> 00:22:08.880
Okay.

00:22:08.930 --> 00:22:10.350
Why don't you go to my place to eat first?

00:22:10.350 --> 00:22:12.030
Right. Your mom is
already cooking at home.

00:22:12.030 --> 00:22:12.890
She's waiting.

00:22:13.480 --> 00:22:14.550
How is your job?

00:22:15.110 --> 00:22:18.070
It's okay. I even wanted to
go to Shanghai to pick you up.

00:22:18.070 --> 00:22:20.920
That won't do. I heard from my senior

00:22:21.270 --> 00:22:23.960
that interns are very busy
when they first join the company.

00:22:23.960 --> 00:22:25.480
You have to be diligent.

00:22:29.400 --> 00:22:30.640
It's good to be back.

00:22:30.720 --> 00:22:32.510
Everything smells so familiar.

00:22:32.510 --> 00:22:33.770
I've really missed it.

00:22:37.310 --> 00:22:38.030
What smell?

00:22:38.310 --> 00:22:39.370
You don't smell it?

00:22:40.110 --> 00:22:42.680
Just a faint hint of water,

00:22:43.000 --> 00:22:43.790
then

00:22:44.510 --> 00:22:46.110
a hint of grass,

00:22:47.160 --> 00:22:48.160
the smell of soil,

00:22:48.350 --> 00:22:50.950
mixed with a bit of
the chemical plant's smell.

00:22:52.400 --> 00:22:53.920
In short, it's the smell of home.

00:22:53.920 --> 00:22:56.920
Different from the osmanthus fragrance
in Shanghai.

00:22:57.070 --> 00:22:59.000
The air is much better now.

00:22:59.510 --> 00:23:00.720
With reduced production and shutdowns,

00:23:00.720 --> 00:23:02.510
those big smokestacks
aren't puffing anymore.

00:23:02.510 --> 00:23:04.160
The smell from the chemical plant
has eased.

00:23:04.160 --> 00:23:07.020
It's picturesque here.
The smell isn't bad either.

00:23:07.550 --> 00:23:10.680
Then, do you prefer
the smell of the chemical plant

00:23:10.680 --> 00:23:13.550
or the fragrance of osmanthus flowers?

00:23:17.350 --> 00:23:18.280
I like them both.

00:23:18.880 --> 00:23:21.300
The chemical plant smell
is the smell of home.

00:23:21.300 --> 00:23:22.360
And home—you always come back to it.

00:23:22.360 --> 00:23:23.620
Nothing can stop that.

00:23:23.750 --> 00:23:25.880
But the osmanthus in Shanghai
smells wonderful too.

00:23:25.880 --> 00:23:26.880
Of course it does.

00:23:27.880 --> 00:23:28.740
What about you?

00:23:30.110 --> 00:23:31.030
Me?

00:23:33.000 --> 00:23:33.960
Look at our home here—

00:23:33.960 --> 00:23:35.270
there are mountains and water.

00:23:35.270 --> 00:23:36.130
And the breeze.

00:23:36.270 --> 00:23:38.550
Then... plus your scent.

00:23:38.830 --> 00:23:41.230
It blends everything together perfectly.

00:23:41.720 --> 00:23:45.400
Just right. I love... this smell.

00:23:45.920 --> 00:23:47.850
Home smells best when you're here.

00:23:55.640 --> 00:23:57.350
Why do I have to
keep waiting for the notice?

00:23:57.350 --> 00:23:58.080
What notice?

00:23:59.440 --> 00:24:00.900
About studying overseas.

00:24:01.110 --> 00:24:02.400
My mom is worried sick.

00:24:02.830 --> 00:24:03.750
Why worry?

00:24:03.750 --> 00:24:06.160
Even if she's worried,
she still has to wait.

00:24:06.160 --> 00:24:06.880
True.

00:24:08.250 --> 00:24:10.110
You're going into your junior year soon.

00:24:10.110 --> 00:24:11.350
Look at Xiaodan—

00:24:12.000 --> 00:24:14.330
going to study abroad and winning awards.

00:24:14.400 --> 00:24:16.160
College isn't like high school.

00:24:16.160 --> 00:24:17.310
You can't just bury yourself in books.

00:24:17.310 --> 00:24:18.910
You have to be more flexible.

00:24:19.350 --> 00:24:20.810
I don't have time for that.

00:24:20.810 --> 00:24:22.350
Didn't you ask me to
take extra finance courses?

00:24:22.350 --> 00:24:24.910
I-I still have to
teach myself computer science.

00:24:24.910 --> 00:24:26.690
Well, we can just aim for grad school.

00:24:26.690 --> 00:24:28.070
After that,
get into a state-owned enterprise

00:24:28.070 --> 00:24:29.200
and find a good unit.

00:24:30.110 --> 00:24:31.350
That will be so stable.

00:24:31.350 --> 00:24:32.030
Mom,

00:24:32.110 --> 00:24:34.960
guaranteed jobs aren't as secure as
they used to be.

00:24:34.960 --> 00:24:36.960
Foreign companies work too, right?

00:24:36.980 --> 00:24:38.560
Many offer good benefits.

00:24:39.510 --> 00:24:40.110
Just think,

00:24:40.110 --> 00:24:42.550
if we had o-one more room,

00:24:42.870 --> 00:24:44.640
relatives could stay over when they visit.

00:24:44.640 --> 00:24:45.570
Don't you agree?

00:24:48.720 --> 00:24:50.520
I'm heading to Xiaoman's place.

00:24:53.830 --> 00:24:54.870
Work hard.

00:24:54.960 --> 00:24:57.160
We're counting on you for a bigger house.

00:24:57.160 --> 00:24:58.790
Okay, a bigger house.

00:25:02.750 --> 00:25:03.890
Be careful on the road.

00:25:03.890 --> 00:25:05.550
I'm off. You should go back up.

00:25:08.750 --> 00:25:10.350
No. I can't live without her!

00:25:10.510 --> 00:25:11.110
Calm down!

00:25:11.110 --> 00:25:11.960
Xia Lei, I beg you!

00:25:11.960 --> 00:25:13.480
Don't make me lose my temper!

00:25:13.480 --> 00:25:14.030
Xia Lei!

00:25:14.030 --> 00:25:14.830
What's wrong?

00:25:14.920 --> 00:25:16.750
I need... I need to find Lulu!

00:25:16.750 --> 00:25:17.350
Wait for Xiaoman to come back!

00:25:17.350 --> 00:25:18.350
I can't live without her.

00:25:18.350 --> 00:25:19.350
The three of us will
help you figure something out!

00:25:19.350 --> 00:25:20.610
I don't need your help!

00:25:20.880 --> 00:25:21.960
I can figure something out myself!

00:25:21.960 --> 00:25:22.750
What are you doing? Why are you shouting?

00:25:22.750 --> 00:25:24.480
What's wrong? What's going on?

00:25:24.640 --> 00:25:25.110
What's wrong?

00:25:25.110 --> 00:25:26.110
Why are you two fighting?

00:25:26.110 --> 00:25:26.960
Calm down. Go have a seat.

00:25:26.960 --> 00:25:28.090
Just sit down first!

00:25:28.310 --> 00:25:30.310
I can't sit! Something big happened!

00:25:30.310 --> 00:25:31.000
-What's wrong?
-Sit down.

00:25:31.000 --> 00:25:32.330
Lulu ran away from home!

00:25:32.430 --> 00:25:33.880
Why make a fuss over this small matter?

00:25:33.880 --> 00:25:35.310
Lulu ran away from home!

00:25:35.440 --> 00:25:37.440
What happened? Why did she run away?

00:25:37.720 --> 00:25:39.640
Business at the plant
hasn't been good lately.

00:25:39.640 --> 00:25:41.070
Her mom wants us to buy an apartment!

00:25:41.070 --> 00:25:42.000
Why buy an apartment?

00:25:42.000 --> 00:25:43.920
Our plant assigns housing, so why bother?

00:25:43.920 --> 00:25:44.920
They stopped assigning housing ages ago.

00:25:44.920 --> 00:25:47.480
Right! Her mom wants us to
buy a place in Tiecheng!

00:25:47.480 --> 00:25:49.750
But we aren't in a hurry!

00:25:49.750 --> 00:25:51.640
We won't get married for a few years!

00:25:51.640 --> 00:25:52.570
But a couple of days ago,

00:25:52.570 --> 00:25:53.880
one of her friends told her

00:25:53.880 --> 00:25:55.750
that you can make good money in the South!

00:25:55.750 --> 00:25:56.510
And she believed it

00:25:56.510 --> 00:25:57.830
and was dead set on going south!

00:25:57.830 --> 00:25:59.070
W-W-Why go there?

00:25:59.070 --> 00:26:00.830
Who actually makes money in the South?

00:26:00.830 --> 00:26:03.400
If it were really that easy,
everyone would've gone. Sit!

00:26:03.400 --> 00:26:03.920
What's really going on?

00:26:03.920 --> 00:26:05.070
-Calm down.
-Say it calmly.

00:26:05.070 --> 00:26:06.350
Tell us, and we'll see what's going on.

00:26:06.350 --> 00:26:09.070
I just had a bad attitude that day

00:26:09.090 --> 00:26:10.880
and said things in the heat of the moment.

00:26:10.880 --> 00:26:13.490
I told her—if you go, we're done.

00:26:13.640 --> 00:26:14.550
Serves you right!

00:26:14.550 --> 00:26:16.110
And you came out with "we're done."

00:26:16.110 --> 00:26:18.350
Can you just throw words like that around?

00:26:18.350 --> 00:26:21.070
No matter how much a couple argues,
no matter how mad or heated things get,

00:26:21.070 --> 00:26:22.470
does saying "we're done"

00:26:22.510 --> 00:26:23.440
solve anything?

00:26:23.700 --> 00:26:24.880
And yet you said, "We're done."

00:26:24.880 --> 00:26:26.350
She must be so disappointed.

00:26:26.350 --> 00:26:26.880
No, no...

00:26:26.920 --> 00:26:27.960
Xiaodan is right.

00:26:28.070 --> 00:26:29.510
-I'm a jerk!
-Right about what?

00:26:29.510 --> 00:26:30.350
Listen...

00:26:31.310 --> 00:26:34.440
let's not be misled by how things look.

00:26:35.510 --> 00:26:39.320
The first day she told you her friends
in the South were making big money.

00:26:39.320 --> 00:26:40.960
The next day she picked a fight

00:26:40.960 --> 00:26:41.830
with you.

00:26:42.160 --> 00:26:45.890
And the morning after that,
she was already off to the South, right?

00:26:48.370 --> 00:26:48.750
What do you mean?

00:26:48.750 --> 00:26:49.960
Wasn't this all planned in advance?

00:26:49.960 --> 00:26:51.960
Buying a ticket takes time, doesn't it?

00:26:51.960 --> 00:26:53.510
She left the day after the fight—

00:26:53.510 --> 00:26:55.110
how could she have done that so quickly?

00:26:55.110 --> 00:26:56.770
So she didn't go to make money?

00:26:58.550 --> 00:27:00.150
-Oh, no, no...
-Is my analysis wrong?

00:27:00.150 --> 00:27:01.480
Xia Lei, what do I do?

00:27:01.510 --> 00:27:02.510
W-Was I wrong?

00:27:02.510 --> 00:27:03.960
Okay, okay. What are you doing?

00:27:03.960 --> 00:27:05.560
W-Why are you getting angry?

00:27:06.270 --> 00:27:07.920
I was just trying to console Dongdong.

00:27:07.920 --> 00:27:09.380
Why are you... hitting me?

00:27:10.350 --> 00:27:11.000
No.

00:27:11.720 --> 00:27:13.270
I just saw the two of them break up

00:27:13.270 --> 00:27:14.460
like that, and I...

00:27:15.160 --> 00:27:16.590
I thought of us.

00:27:16.830 --> 00:27:19.380
I was thinking,
no matter what happens in the future,

00:27:19.380 --> 00:27:21.000
we should never say such hurtful things
to each other.

00:27:21.000 --> 00:27:22.000
You scared me.

00:27:22.160 --> 00:27:23.790
I won't. Don't worry.

00:27:24.070 --> 00:27:25.720
Even though we're far apart,

00:27:26.000 --> 00:27:27.930
I would never say things like that.

00:27:28.790 --> 00:27:29.270
If you get mad,

00:27:29.270 --> 00:27:30.960
I'll run after you
and make it up to you right away.

00:27:30.960 --> 00:27:31.350
Okay?

00:27:31.750 --> 00:27:32.150
I'm telling you—

00:27:32.150 --> 00:27:34.350
when you argue, your head

00:27:34.830 --> 00:27:35.680
just overheats,

00:27:35.680 --> 00:27:36.510
and you say those things without thinking.

00:27:36.510 --> 00:27:37.170
We're over.

00:27:43.160 --> 00:27:44.290
I'll drink with you.

00:27:48.880 --> 00:27:50.400
We're over.

00:27:51.270 --> 00:27:52.070
It's all over.

00:27:52.640 --> 00:27:53.840
The plant has no work.

00:27:54.110 --> 00:27:55.550
With this little salary,
how can I afford a house?

00:27:55.550 --> 00:27:56.410
Wang Dongdong!

00:27:57.070 --> 00:27:58.550
Why are you making a scene here?

00:27:58.550 --> 00:27:59.350
Get up!

00:27:59.580 --> 00:28:00.840
I can't drink anymore.

00:28:01.160 --> 00:28:02.420
I'm seeing things now.

00:28:02.480 --> 00:28:04.610
She's probably at Shanhaiguan by now.

00:28:04.960 --> 00:28:06.680
I'll slap you all the way to Shanhaiguan!

00:28:06.680 --> 00:28:07.160
You loser,

00:28:07.160 --> 00:28:08.070
get up!

00:28:08.880 --> 00:28:10.750
Get up... Have you no shame?

00:28:10.750 --> 00:28:12.160
Why are you making a scene here?

00:28:12.160 --> 00:28:14.590
Lulu? You didn't leave?

00:28:15.350 --> 00:28:18.400
I thought you left! Where were you?

00:28:18.420 --> 00:28:19.290
Sit down!

00:28:19.640 --> 00:28:21.160
Suddenly, his eyes are clear.
You calm down now, huh?

00:28:21.160 --> 00:28:21.790
Sit here.

00:28:23.960 --> 00:28:26.070
Didn't you say we're done? Let's break up.

00:28:26.070 --> 00:28:27.420
That's... that's not what I meant.

00:28:27.420 --> 00:28:28.100
I mean...

00:28:28.350 --> 00:28:29.720
Why do I want to go south?

00:28:29.880 --> 00:28:31.270
What's wrong with me wanting to go south?

00:28:31.270 --> 00:28:33.180
Is it wrong for my mom
to want a better life for her daughter?

00:28:33.180 --> 00:28:34.640
Besides, look at Xiaodan.

00:28:35.350 --> 00:28:37.510
She came back from the South,
from Shanghai.

00:28:37.510 --> 00:28:39.970
I've never even seen
the cosmetics she uses!

00:28:40.050 --> 00:28:42.480
You sit around cracking
sunflower seeds all day, not working hard,

00:28:42.480 --> 00:28:44.350
and all the pressure falls on me!

00:28:44.350 --> 00:28:45.310
What am I supposed to do?

00:28:45.310 --> 00:28:47.400
I just wanted a better life for us!

00:28:47.440 --> 00:28:48.640
-Say something. Hurry up!
-I... I was wrong.

00:28:48.640 --> 00:28:49.240
I... um...

00:28:49.310 --> 00:28:50.910
Do you think it's easy for me?

00:28:50.960 --> 00:28:52.070
D-Don't we have a house?

00:28:52.070 --> 00:28:53.330
The plant staff house.

00:28:53.400 --> 00:28:54.270
We can fix it up,

00:28:54.510 --> 00:28:56.240
then get our marriage licenses

00:28:56.400 --> 00:28:57.790
so we can put our parents' minds at ease!

00:28:57.790 --> 00:28:59.590
Who said they're "our" parents?

00:29:00.180 --> 00:29:01.520
I... I will definitely...

00:29:01.520 --> 00:29:02.070
I will definitely...

00:29:02.070 --> 00:29:04.030
save money. I'll save a lot of money.

00:29:04.030 --> 00:29:05.830
I'll design the house
Dad left us properly.

00:29:05.830 --> 00:29:06.640
Stop rambling.

00:29:06.640 --> 00:29:07.680
-Dongdong has already planned it out.
-Right.

00:29:07.680 --> 00:29:08.680
His family's place
will be your marital home.

00:29:08.680 --> 00:29:09.960
-He even wants to redesign it for you.
-Yeah.

00:29:09.960 --> 00:29:11.350
He'll fix up your place nicely

00:29:11.350 --> 00:29:12.000
and live a good life with you.

00:29:12.000 --> 00:29:13.590
He asked me to design that place.

00:29:13.590 --> 00:29:14.400
I've taken the job.

00:29:14.400 --> 00:29:15.720
I'll design it nicely for you two.

00:29:15.720 --> 00:29:16.720
You're just taking his side.

00:29:16.720 --> 00:29:17.790
Xiaodan studied this!

00:29:17.790 --> 00:29:18.350
Why would I lie to you?

00:29:18.350 --> 00:29:20.070
Right, right! I've thought it all through.

00:29:20.070 --> 00:29:22.160
We'll fix the place up nicely,

00:29:22.160 --> 00:29:24.110
and it'll be our home when we get married.

00:29:24.110 --> 00:29:25.160
Then, we'll spend this summer

00:29:25.160 --> 00:29:26.070
getting it all fixed up for you.

00:29:26.070 --> 00:29:27.350
You can just live there for now.

00:29:27.350 --> 00:29:29.020
Right. Don't... don't be mad anymore.

00:29:29.020 --> 00:29:29.880
Sit down. Sit.

00:29:29.880 --> 00:29:31.400
Come on, have a seat.

00:29:31.510 --> 00:29:33.440
Stay a while. H-H-Have a bottle.

00:29:33.640 --> 00:29:34.110
Cool off.

00:29:34.110 --> 00:29:34.750
Let's have a drink.

00:29:34.750 --> 00:29:36.080
Eat something. Come on.

00:29:36.160 --> 00:29:37.720
Calm down. Open a bottle for her!

00:29:37.720 --> 00:29:40.250
Just tear down everything
in the yard, right?

00:29:42.720 --> 00:29:43.630
Here we go!

00:29:43.630 --> 00:29:48.640
♪ Walk on the same road a thousand times ♪

00:29:48.640 --> 00:29:49.000
Keep playing.

00:29:49.000 --> 00:29:50.840
I wonder how those two are getting on
with the demolition.

00:29:50.840 --> 00:29:57.400
♪ Run together and venture
to the distant mountains ♪

00:29:57.970 --> 00:29:58.440
♪ We yearn for tomorrow
yet cling to yesterday ♪

00:29:58.440 --> 00:29:59.070
Xiaoman!

00:29:59.510 --> 00:30:00.640
-How far have you gotten?
-Xiaodan!

00:30:00.640 --> 00:30:02.720
-Let me see how it's coming along.
-Xia Lei!

00:30:02.720 --> 00:30:03.720
Let me check...

00:30:03.750 --> 00:30:04.830
Come in and take a look.

00:30:04.830 --> 00:30:05.640
We're helping you move stuff out, right?

00:30:05.640 --> 00:30:05.670
Right, right.

00:30:05.670 --> 00:30:06.510
♪ Leaves blown away by the wind ♪

00:30:06.510 --> 00:30:07.110
How is it?

00:30:07.350 --> 00:30:08.510
Right? Just move all these out.

00:30:08.510 --> 00:30:09.510
Tear this wall down

00:30:09.510 --> 00:30:11.970
so the lighting
will be much better that way.

00:30:12.070 --> 00:30:12.550
Okay.

00:30:12.630 --> 00:30:13.480
♪ Spin and spin, spin a few circles
back to the starting point ♪

00:30:13.480 --> 00:30:14.160
Careful, Uncle.

00:30:14.160 --> 00:30:15.160
I'm fine. I got it.

00:30:16.830 --> 00:30:18.750
Xiaodan, you go out.
It's too dusty in here!

00:30:18.750 --> 00:30:19.280
Let me see how we can redesign this part.

00:30:19.280 --> 00:30:25.800
♪ Save and save, accumulate bitterness
to exchange for sweetness ♪

00:30:26.780 --> 00:30:33.580
♪ When will we stand side by side again,
and when will we say goodbye? ♪

00:30:34.500 --> 00:30:40.370
♪ Like the swaying swing ♪

00:30:41.180 --> 00:30:44.310
♪ If seas turn to mulberry fields ♪

00:30:44.310 --> 00:30:45.070
Xiaoman!

00:30:45.210 --> 00:30:46.680
♪ Whether flat or winding ♪

00:30:46.680 --> 00:30:47.510
Come here.

00:30:48.700 --> 00:30:51.550
♪ If rain wets your face ♪

00:30:51.550 --> 00:30:52.640
Do you remember

00:30:52.690 --> 00:30:53.000
♪ Chat at the old spot
after all storms have passed ♪

00:30:53.000 --> 00:30:54.660
the size of that window?

00:30:54.880 --> 00:30:55.680
Which window?

00:30:55.790 --> 00:30:56.880
T-The one by the door.

00:30:56.880 --> 00:30:58.830
I forgot the size.
Was it one meter by how wide?

00:30:58.830 --> 00:30:59.480
This one?

00:30:59.510 --> 00:31:00.480
♪ Time train goes round and round ♪

00:31:00.480 --> 00:31:01.810
One meter by one twenty.

00:31:03.260 --> 00:31:03.880
♪ Day by day, year by year ♪

00:31:03.880 --> 00:31:05.480
The drawing is so detailed.

00:31:07.000 --> 00:31:07.110
♪ Wave your hands and stride ahead ♪

00:31:07.110 --> 00:31:08.000
Awesome.

00:31:10.680 --> 00:31:10.790
♪ The years are kind ♪

00:31:10.790 --> 00:31:11.880
When you're free,

00:31:12.240 --> 00:31:14.400
design our house too.

00:31:14.400 --> 00:31:15.030
♪ Migratory birds fly over
the mountain top ♪

00:31:15.030 --> 00:31:16.290
We should renovate it.

00:31:17.870 --> 00:31:18.520
♪ Get through the coldest day ♪

00:31:18.520 --> 00:31:20.000
Then I want a small studio.

00:31:20.780 --> 00:31:21.510
A studio?

00:31:22.200 --> 00:31:23.410
We'll turn the whole house into a studio.

00:31:23.410 --> 00:31:23.960
♪ Wait till the kapok blooms ♪

00:31:23.960 --> 00:31:24.880
Just leave me a sofa.

00:31:24.880 --> 00:31:26.210
I'll sit there with you.

00:31:27.270 --> 00:31:30.400
♪ When you come rushing back still ♪

00:31:31.160 --> 00:31:32.550
♪ The young you ♪

00:31:32.550 --> 00:31:33.480
What's that for?

00:31:33.640 --> 00:31:34.440
To thank you.

00:31:34.830 --> 00:31:35.480
Xiaoman!

00:31:35.640 --> 00:31:36.720
What?

00:31:37.070 --> 00:31:37.960
Hurry up and come here!

00:31:37.960 --> 00:31:38.830
Take a look at this door for me.

00:31:38.830 --> 00:31:41.130
I want to remove it,
but I can't figure out how.

00:31:41.130 --> 00:31:41.880
Just stay right here.

00:31:41.880 --> 00:31:43.340
Come and take a look for me.

00:31:43.400 --> 00:31:44.110
Coming.

00:31:44.330 --> 00:31:46.530
Come on. We can't do without you. Hurry.

00:31:47.590 --> 00:31:49.920
Look at this door.
I wanted to tear it down,

00:31:50.320 --> 00:31:51.670
but I just don't know how.

00:31:51.670 --> 00:31:54.000
What's all this about tearing down a door?

00:31:58.320 --> 00:31:58.930
Let's go.

00:31:58.960 --> 00:32:00.620
-Let me take a look.
-Careful.

00:32:00.640 --> 00:32:02.030
Don't go any further.

00:32:02.030 --> 00:32:02.880
-Wait a second.
-That's about right.

00:32:02.880 --> 00:32:03.200
What?

00:32:03.200 --> 00:32:04.880
-That's about right.
-The surprise has to hit full impact.

00:32:04.880 --> 00:32:05.920
-Tie this over her eyes.
-My goodness.

00:32:05.920 --> 00:32:07.020
-No peeking.
-All this.

00:32:07.020 --> 00:32:08.240
-No peeking.
-Cover her eyes!

00:32:08.240 --> 00:32:09.370
These young people.

00:32:10.270 --> 00:32:11.530
A step. Watch the step.

00:32:11.640 --> 00:32:12.510
Be careful.

00:32:14.070 --> 00:32:15.270
Pulling off a big surprise here.

00:32:15.270 --> 00:32:15.730
Come in.

00:32:15.830 --> 00:32:17.920
So mysterious. Should I step in?

00:32:18.030 --> 00:32:18.690
Be careful.

00:32:19.510 --> 00:32:20.240
Okay, I'm in.

00:32:20.310 --> 00:32:21.200
Surprise time.

00:32:21.220 --> 00:32:22.530
It even smells nice in here.

00:32:22.530 --> 00:32:23.330
Are you ready?

00:32:23.960 --> 00:32:24.680
I'm ready.

00:32:28.090 --> 00:32:31.350
♪ If seas turn to mulberry fields ♪

00:32:31.350 --> 00:32:31.750
I...

00:32:32.150 --> 00:32:32.550
♪ Whether flat or winding ♪

00:32:32.550 --> 00:32:33.110
What do you think?

00:32:33.110 --> 00:32:33.880
What do you think? Wait a second.

00:32:33.880 --> 00:32:35.210
Let me put on my glasses.

00:32:35.310 --> 00:32:35.500
Take a good look.

00:32:35.500 --> 00:32:39.230
♪ If rain wets your face ♪

00:32:39.250 --> 00:32:41.270
♪ Chat at the old spot
after all storms have passed ♪

00:32:41.270 --> 00:32:43.750
Oh my god, this is so great!

00:32:46.140 --> 00:32:49.970
♪ Time train goes round and round ♪

00:32:50.020 --> 00:32:53.040
♪ Day by day, year by year ♪

00:32:53.700 --> 00:32:57.530
♪ Wave your hands and stride ahead ♪

00:32:57.560 --> 00:33:01.010
♪ There'll be sunshine through the years ♪

00:33:01.030 --> 00:33:04.490
♪ Migratory birds fly over
the mountain top ♪

00:33:04.520 --> 00:33:08.440
♪ Survive the coldest day ♪

00:33:10.050 --> 00:33:13.700
♪ Wait till the kapok blooms ♪

00:33:13.910 --> 00:33:17.500
♪ When you come rushing back still ♪

00:33:17.880 --> 00:33:20.070
♪ The young you ♪

00:33:20.070 --> 00:33:20.510
Hello?

00:33:21.590 --> 00:33:22.030
Mom.

00:33:23.680 --> 00:33:25.000
This goes all the way through.

00:33:25.000 --> 00:33:25.930
Yeah. Two doors!

00:33:26.000 --> 00:33:27.200
There's even a little pavilion here!

00:33:27.200 --> 00:33:29.020
This is wonderful!
Look at all the flowers!

00:33:29.020 --> 00:33:30.420
-Come on.
-Let's go down.

00:33:32.510 --> 00:33:35.280
Mr. Ding, we can come down directly
from over there!

00:33:35.280 --> 00:33:36.750
Really. Look, there's a ladder here!

00:33:36.750 --> 00:33:38.080
We can go straight down.

00:33:39.330 --> 00:33:41.170
God, Xiaodan is so impressive!

00:33:41.200 --> 00:33:42.270
She really knows her stuff.

00:33:42.270 --> 00:33:43.200
She designed it.

00:33:43.240 --> 00:33:44.290
Do you like it, Lulu?

00:33:44.290 --> 00:33:44.970
I do!

00:33:45.000 --> 00:33:46.480
That's all that matters!

00:33:46.480 --> 00:33:47.660
I have to treat you guys
to a big meal later.

00:33:47.660 --> 00:33:48.590
Let's talk about that later,

00:33:48.590 --> 00:33:50.480
but you can't hit Dongdong anymore.

00:33:50.480 --> 00:33:51.370
I didn't hit him.

00:33:51.370 --> 00:33:51.920
It's okay.

00:33:51.920 --> 00:33:54.610
There're two beds anyway.
If she hits me, we'll just sleep apart.

00:33:54.610 --> 00:33:55.000
I didn't hit him.

00:33:55.000 --> 00:33:56.200
I'm at Dongdong's place.

00:33:56.200 --> 00:33:58.590
Didn't I design their marital home?

00:33:58.720 --> 00:34:00.980
It's finished, and we came to take a look.

00:34:09.320 --> 00:34:11.010
Where did she go to take the call...

00:34:11.010 --> 00:34:12.409
She's still on the phone.

00:34:13.530 --> 00:34:15.320
You have to admit
Xiaodan is something else.

00:34:15.320 --> 00:34:15.989
Look at this kid.

00:34:15.989 --> 00:34:16.710
She hasn't been learning for long,

00:34:16.710 --> 00:34:18.909
but look at her work. It's the real deal.

00:34:19.440 --> 00:34:21.550
She's always had a knack for everything

00:34:21.550 --> 00:34:22.679
she sets her mind to.

00:34:23.480 --> 00:34:24.340
What about you?

00:34:25.190 --> 00:34:26.000
What about me?

00:34:26.520 --> 00:34:27.550
You need to get closer
to the organization.

00:34:27.550 --> 00:34:28.780
Such a great organization.

00:34:28.780 --> 00:34:29.480
Great as she is,

00:34:29.480 --> 00:34:30.810
isn't she already mine?

00:34:31.800 --> 00:34:33.330
You're so sure of yourself.

00:34:36.710 --> 00:34:38.440
It got approved? That's great.

00:34:39.590 --> 00:34:42.710
Xiaoman, my mom said
my application for studying overseas

00:34:42.710 --> 00:34:43.710
was approved!

00:34:44.110 --> 00:34:44.840
Really?

00:34:45.360 --> 00:34:47.110
See? She just keeps
getting more impressive.

00:34:47.110 --> 00:34:50.480
Study overseas.
S-She's going abroad to study.

00:34:51.730 --> 00:34:52.739
Going overseas?

00:34:53.440 --> 00:34:53.880
Going overseas...

00:34:53.880 --> 00:34:55.480
Study... Study overseas...
Learning to swim?

00:34:55.480 --> 00:34:55.800
Swimming... in the sea?

00:34:55.800 --> 00:34:57.590
W-Why go abroad to learn swimming?

00:34:57.590 --> 00:35:00.190
Can't we do that here?
What will you do after going abroad?

00:35:00.190 --> 00:35:02.050
It's a short-term study program!

00:35:02.480 --> 00:35:04.030
Just going overseas to see the world,
have a look around.

00:35:04.030 --> 00:35:05.760
I'll be back in about two weeks.

00:35:06.400 --> 00:35:08.330
Well, she gets to go abroad anyway.

00:35:08.400 --> 00:35:09.130
Impressive.

00:35:17.850 --> 00:35:18.880
I haven't stayed long enough.

00:35:18.880 --> 00:35:21.070
It's only been a few days,
and I'm already leaving.

00:35:21.070 --> 00:35:22.480
Come back again next time.

00:35:22.480 --> 00:35:24.400
Going abroad is such a good opportunity.

00:35:24.400 --> 00:35:27.400
Visiting so many countries in 15 days.
How wonderful.

00:35:28.070 --> 00:35:28.960
Then what do you want?

00:35:28.960 --> 00:35:29.670
I'll bring you something back.

00:35:29.670 --> 00:35:30.710
I don't want anything.

00:35:30.710 --> 00:35:33.190
Eat well while you're there.

00:35:33.400 --> 00:35:35.110
Don't get cold, and stay safe.

00:35:35.170 --> 00:35:37.030
Don't worry about anything else.

00:35:39.550 --> 00:35:40.710
I hate to leave.

00:35:41.880 --> 00:35:42.820
Don't be like that.

00:35:42.820 --> 00:35:43.670
When there's a chance in the future,

00:35:43.670 --> 00:35:45.670
I'll go with you and travel abroad.

00:35:45.670 --> 00:35:47.550
That place, Venice, right?

00:35:48.190 --> 00:35:50.190
And the Eiffel Tower in France.

00:35:50.190 --> 00:35:51.390
We'll go see them all.

00:35:57.550 --> 00:35:59.280
It's okay. Don't be afraid.

00:36:00.190 --> 00:36:01.480
Take care of yourself.

00:36:03.180 --> 00:36:03.880
Give it to me.

00:36:03.880 --> 00:36:05.610
Let's go. I'll carry it. Let me.

00:36:07.110 --> 00:36:08.310
I'll just walk her up.

00:36:10.670 --> 00:36:11.200
Let's go.

00:36:11.400 --> 00:36:13.550
Get on the train first. Get on. Let's go.

00:36:13.550 --> 00:36:14.000
No.

00:36:14.440 --> 00:36:14.970
Let's go.

00:36:15.550 --> 00:36:16.590
Get on the train.

00:36:52.630 --> 00:36:53.150
Come in.

00:36:56.550 --> 00:36:57.990
Is Mr. Xia, Xia Lei, here?

00:36:58.670 --> 00:36:59.110
Yes...

00:37:00.630 --> 00:37:01.480
Are you crazy?

00:37:07.400 --> 00:37:08.730
I have good news for you.

00:37:09.400 --> 00:37:10.400
What is it?

00:37:11.110 --> 00:37:12.520
We made money.

00:37:16.360 --> 00:37:17.960
We finally saw some returns?

00:37:19.150 --> 00:37:19.710
How much?

00:37:19.730 --> 00:37:20.210
Guess.

00:37:22.400 --> 00:37:23.330
A hundred thousand?

00:37:23.330 --> 00:37:24.790
Are you crazy about money?

00:37:26.550 --> 00:37:27.110
Eighty thousand?

00:37:27.110 --> 00:37:28.970
Eight thousand! Eight thousand!

00:37:29.190 --> 00:37:31.120
Eight thousand yuan is still a lot.

00:37:32.590 --> 00:37:33.650
What are you doing?

00:37:33.800 --> 00:37:35.840
I came across a factory on the website...

00:37:35.840 --> 00:37:37.570
that sells gas stove brackets.

00:37:37.960 --> 00:37:39.400
I'm thinking of contacting them
for my buddy

00:37:39.400 --> 00:37:41.480
to see if I can get him a welding job.

00:37:48.190 --> 00:37:49.000
Lei.

00:37:50.110 --> 00:37:53.040
I've realized that you really are
a business genius.

00:37:54.280 --> 00:37:55.210
What do you mean?

00:37:55.800 --> 00:37:58.110
I mean... in the future, our website

00:37:58.140 --> 00:37:59.960
can not only integrate resources

00:37:59.960 --> 00:38:03.620
but also help clients
connect with factories and refer business.

00:38:03.920 --> 00:38:05.930
Don't you think it's worth exploring?

00:38:05.930 --> 00:38:08.390
I'm just trying to
find my buddy a job. You...

00:38:08.870 --> 00:38:09.860
Let me think.

00:38:10.190 --> 00:38:11.230
I think it's time for our company

00:38:11.230 --> 00:38:13.070
to expand and upgrade.

00:38:13.670 --> 00:38:15.800
That direction will definitely work.

00:38:15.890 --> 00:38:16.400
Alright then.

00:38:16.400 --> 00:38:18.440
Let me reach out
to the factory first and see.

00:38:18.440 --> 00:38:20.490
If the initial contact goes well...

00:38:21.800 --> 00:38:23.440
-we can talk more about it then.
-Contact them now.

00:38:23.440 --> 00:38:24.190
Call them right now.

00:38:24.190 --> 00:38:25.630
Come on. Let's contact them now.

00:38:25.630 --> 00:38:27.190
I've never contacted clients before.

00:38:27.190 --> 00:38:28.670
I-It's always been you.

00:38:28.880 --> 00:38:30.710
You are a boss, too.

00:38:30.880 --> 00:38:31.610
I can't do it.

00:38:31.800 --> 00:38:32.670
Why can't you?

00:38:32.670 --> 00:38:33.400
You can do it!

00:38:33.400 --> 00:38:35.000
You have to meet clients sooner or later.

00:38:35.000 --> 00:38:36.070
I can't do it every time!

00:38:36.070 --> 00:38:36.670
You can do it.

00:38:36.670 --> 00:38:38.320
You're the best!

00:38:38.340 --> 00:38:39.650
Come on. You got this.

00:38:41.800 --> 00:38:42.530
You can do it.

00:38:44.480 --> 00:38:45.340
Don't wimp out.

00:38:51.090 --> 00:38:52.290
You got this. Come on.

00:38:57.630 --> 00:38:58.230
Use this.

00:38:59.320 --> 00:38:59.840
Take it.

00:39:00.440 --> 00:39:02.440
I won this as an award at the plant.

00:39:03.590 --> 00:39:04.440
I don't need it, Mentor.

00:39:04.440 --> 00:39:05.550
You keep it. Keep it.

00:39:05.550 --> 00:39:06.000
Oh, come on.

00:39:06.000 --> 00:39:06.710
Look at yours.

00:39:06.710 --> 00:39:08.530
From a distance,
you'd think it was a discus.

00:39:08.530 --> 00:39:09.590
Can it even be used?

00:39:09.590 --> 00:39:10.850
This one is new. Use it.

00:39:12.110 --> 00:39:12.930
Thank you, Mentor.

00:39:12.930 --> 00:39:13.930
Don't mention it.

00:39:14.960 --> 00:39:16.290
Still distracted, huh?

00:39:17.150 --> 00:39:18.070
The day before yesterday,
we turned the soil.

00:39:18.070 --> 00:39:20.070
Yesterday we put up the trellis
for the tomatoes.

00:39:20.070 --> 00:39:21.800
If you really feel so idle today,

00:39:21.800 --> 00:39:22.710
go fertilize them.

00:39:22.710 --> 00:39:24.000
You could fertilize them yourself.

00:39:24.000 --> 00:39:24.840
I'm not going.

00:39:25.070 --> 00:39:28.200
Mentor, I've been
thinking about something these days.

00:39:28.550 --> 00:39:30.000
Uh, Xia Lei,

00:39:30.110 --> 00:39:32.240
didn't he set up a website in Shanghai?

00:39:32.870 --> 00:39:34.240
So I asked him to help me check

00:39:34.240 --> 00:39:35.370
if there's any work

00:39:35.400 --> 00:39:36.670
our plant can handle.

00:39:37.320 --> 00:39:38.400
And he actually found one.

00:39:38.400 --> 00:39:41.000
There's this gas stove factory.

00:39:41.330 --> 00:39:43.640
They need brackets for the gas stoves.

00:39:44.280 --> 00:39:47.080
Do you think our plant
can handle that kind of work?

00:39:47.360 --> 00:39:48.440
Absolutely.

00:39:49.070 --> 00:39:50.070
Machining, fitting, riveting, and welding—

00:39:50.070 --> 00:39:51.070
those skills will feed you anywhere.

00:39:51.070 --> 00:39:52.670
Besides, for these people of ours,

00:39:52.670 --> 00:39:54.630
welding mere brackets for gas stoves?

00:39:54.630 --> 00:39:56.000
They're so overqualified.

00:39:56.000 --> 00:39:57.280
Totally a piece of cake!

00:39:57.280 --> 00:39:58.000
Alright then.

00:39:58.000 --> 00:39:59.130
I'll go talk to them.

00:39:59.310 --> 00:40:01.030
How about I invite
Wang Dongdong from Workshop 2

00:40:01.030 --> 00:40:01.710
to join us?

00:40:02.800 --> 00:40:04.340
Call him. It's not easy for anyone.

00:40:04.340 --> 00:40:05.230
Money earned is money earned.

00:40:05.230 --> 00:40:05.670
Okay.

00:40:05.800 --> 00:40:06.590
After lunch,

00:40:06.590 --> 00:40:08.250
I'll bring it to the director.

00:40:08.440 --> 00:40:09.110
Go to him?

00:40:09.680 --> 00:40:10.260
You don't need to

00:40:10.260 --> 00:40:10.860
go ask him.

00:40:10.860 --> 00:40:12.520
He'll definitely be on board.

00:40:13.190 --> 00:40:16.050
After all, that will also
count as his performance!

00:40:16.070 --> 00:40:17.130
Come on, come here.

00:40:17.560 --> 00:40:18.080
Come on!

00:40:21.160 --> 00:40:22.030
Fill it up for this kid!

00:40:22.030 --> 00:40:22.690
Sure thing.

00:40:24.370 --> 00:40:25.570
Try the new lunch box.

00:40:27.440 --> 00:40:28.110
My brain

00:40:28.110 --> 00:40:29.970
just can't come up with any ideas.

00:40:32.230 --> 00:40:34.090
It's okay. I'm thinking about it.

00:40:34.880 --> 00:40:36.940
What could you possibly come up with?

00:40:37.500 --> 00:40:38.310
It's alright.

00:40:38.970 --> 00:40:39.670
He's coming.

00:40:39.670 --> 00:40:42.130
It should be fine.
He looks quite confident.

00:40:50.190 --> 00:40:50.920
How did it go?

00:40:55.400 --> 00:40:58.230
No. The director just flat-out refused.

00:40:58.800 --> 00:41:00.130
He just wouldn't agree.

00:41:00.440 --> 00:41:03.030
He kept saying there was no sincerity.

00:41:03.030 --> 00:41:06.190
Where am I supposed to
find the sincerity in something like this?

00:41:06.190 --> 00:41:07.400
I'm telling you—

00:41:07.400 --> 00:41:09.280
if you transfer money to his account,

00:41:09.280 --> 00:41:10.340
that's sincerity.

00:41:11.230 --> 00:41:12.490
Wait, what do you mean?

00:41:12.880 --> 00:41:14.740
Yeah, that's exactly what I mean.

00:41:15.190 --> 00:41:16.550
What? You mean I'm supposed to
front some money

00:41:16.550 --> 00:41:17.400
before I've even earned anything?

00:41:17.400 --> 00:41:18.000
Right?

00:41:18.070 --> 00:41:20.330
Where would we even get money
to give him?

00:41:20.760 --> 00:41:21.480
Xiaoman,

00:41:21.880 --> 00:41:23.940
have another talk with the director.

00:41:24.400 --> 00:41:27.000
Ask him to let us use
the scraps to get started.

00:41:27.070 --> 00:41:28.880
Once we submit the sample,

00:41:29.110 --> 00:41:31.910
we'll have the money
to show our sincerity. Right?

00:41:32.000 --> 00:41:33.530
Dongdong's idea isn't bad.

00:41:33.550 --> 00:41:34.070
Yeah.

00:41:34.330 --> 00:41:35.230
Give me a break.

00:41:35.230 --> 00:41:36.670
The two of you don't even have

00:41:36.670 --> 00:41:38.200
an ounce of sense combined.

00:41:38.550 --> 00:41:39.400
If we're already doing the work,

00:41:39.400 --> 00:41:40.590
why do we still need to show sincerity?

00:41:40.590 --> 00:41:42.110
Sincerity is supposed to come first!

00:41:42.110 --> 00:41:43.530
We have to show it before we can work.

00:41:43.530 --> 00:41:44.230
Right, right.

00:41:44.230 --> 00:41:46.070
And once it's done, what sincerity
do we need to show him?

00:41:46.070 --> 00:41:47.070
Yeah. Calm down. Let me think.

00:41:47.070 --> 00:41:48.110
I have other ideas.

00:41:48.110 --> 00:41:50.510
Forget it. Wang Dongdong, your brain is
just for decoration.

00:41:50.510 --> 00:41:51.440
Write him an IOU.

00:41:53.910 --> 00:41:54.850
Hurry up and eat.

00:41:54.880 --> 00:41:56.280
Dongdong's idea is good.

00:41:56.950 --> 00:41:57.470
Gosh.

00:41:59.280 --> 00:41:59.880
Director.

00:41:59.880 --> 00:42:00.510
Xiaoman,

00:42:00.880 --> 00:42:02.630
that's absolutely out of the question.

00:42:02.630 --> 00:42:04.480
Director, listen to me.

00:42:04.960 --> 00:42:06.940
We've figured out a way.

00:42:07.110 --> 00:42:08.170
Let's talk inside.

00:42:08.530 --> 00:42:09.730
Director, after you.

00:42:09.960 --> 00:42:10.590
Go in.

00:42:11.190 --> 00:42:13.030
Director, well...

00:42:13.400 --> 00:42:15.710
we've thought this through.

00:42:16.230 --> 00:42:17.280
See if this works.

00:42:17.800 --> 00:42:21.030
First, we'll only work at night.

00:42:21.440 --> 00:42:22.590
We won't do anything during the day.

00:42:22.590 --> 00:42:24.670
We absolutely won't
let other departments see us.

00:42:24.670 --> 00:42:25.150
Right?

00:42:25.230 --> 00:42:26.590
We don't want to cause you trouble

00:42:26.590 --> 00:42:28.110
before anything's even finalized.

00:42:28.110 --> 00:42:29.040
Don't you think?

00:42:29.360 --> 00:42:30.440
Secondly,

00:42:30.590 --> 00:42:32.470
once our sample is done,

00:42:32.960 --> 00:42:34.960
I'll have them pay some money first.

00:42:35.760 --> 00:42:36.510
As a deposit!

00:42:37.400 --> 00:42:39.110
That money is just a gesture.

00:42:39.110 --> 00:42:40.080
A sign of sincerity.

00:42:40.080 --> 00:42:42.410
It won't be deducted

00:42:42.440 --> 00:42:44.340
from future payments or anything.

00:42:44.340 --> 00:42:45.340
What do you think?

00:42:47.670 --> 00:42:48.360
Director, then,

00:42:48.360 --> 00:42:50.920
could you please write down
your account number for me?

00:42:50.920 --> 00:42:51.920
That's for later.

00:42:52.550 --> 00:42:53.480
Just this once.

00:42:56.030 --> 00:42:57.150
Thank you, Director.

00:42:57.150 --> 00:42:57.800
Thank you, Director.

00:42:57.800 --> 00:42:59.660
I'll be going back now, Director.

00:42:59.670 --> 00:43:01.200
-See you, Director.
-Okay.

00:43:02.880 --> 00:43:03.710
Director, I'm off!